* Am I missing something?
* How does this relate to the talk of _programming to an interface_? Some locals here seem to
  think it is relevant, and I agree that it does, just not immediately, as I see it. It is more
  like _programming against an interface_ here, or _against a subclass_ in general. I am a bit at
  a loss about these intricacies.

